title: Short Poetry Collection 114
creator: Various
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox Short Poetry Collection 114. This is a collection of poems read by LibriVox volunteers for November 2012. 01 - Ah Sunflower by William Blake (1757-1827) 02 - The Auld Wife by Charles Stuart Calverley (1831-1884) 03 - An Autumn Rain-Scene by Thomas Hardy (1840-1928) 04 - La Belle Dame Sans Merci by John Keats (1795-1821) 05 - Betty by Lola Ridge (1883-1941) 06 - Companions - A Tale of a Grandfather by Charles Stuart Calverley (1831-1884) 07 - A Coronet for his Mistress Philosophy by George Chapman (1559-1634) 08 - The Death of the Hired Man by Robert Frost (1874-1963) 09 - Drinking Song by John Fletcher (1579-1625) 10 - Fairies by Rose Fyleman (1877-1957) 11 - A Farewell to Arms (to Queen Elizabeth) by George Peele (1558–1597) 12 - L'Homme de l'Ennui by Matilda Betham (1776-1852) 13 - A Hungry Day by Isabella Crawford (1850-1887) 14 - In School Days by John Greenleaf Whittier (1807-92) 15 - The Life Beyond by Rupert Brooke (1887-1915) 16 - Lines Written in Early Spring by William Wordsworth (1770-1850) 17 - The Long Small Room by Edward Thomas (1878-1917) 18 - Longing by Paul Laurence Dunbar (1872-1906) 19 - Love Not Me for my Comely Grace by Unknown 20 - The Negro Speaks of Rivers by Langston Hughes (1902-1967) 21 - The Night by Emily Bronte (1820 – 1849) 22 - Not to Keep by Robert Frost (1874-1963) 23 - An Old Memory by Paul Laurence Dunbar 24 - The Poet by Thomas Randolph (1605-1635) 25 - Rain by Edward Thomas (1878-1917) 26 - The Sirens' Song by William Browne, of Tavistock (1588-1643) 27 - Song of Myself by Walt Whitman (1819-1892) 28 - Terminus by Ralph Waldo Emerson (1803-1882) 29 - Transience by Sarojini Naidu (1879-1949) 30 - Were I A King I Could Command Content by Edward de Vere (1550-1604) 31 - Work Gangs by Carl Sandburg (1878-1967) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
